This paper discusses the design of a data center network architecture, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the design goals of large data centers, such as scalability and high throughput, which are important topics in the field of data center networking (cs.DC). The proposed architecture also involves routing protocols, which can be categorized under the subfield of network protocols and algorithms (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of key-based routing, which is a topic in the field of cryptography and security (cs.AR). Finally, the paper discusses the experimental evaluation of the proposed architecture, which involves performance analysis and optimization, falling under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
